/* Description */There's actually not a single verse on the Quran prohibiting children to inherit from their adoptive parents. Also, Quran prioritizes bequest rather inheritance, which by definition allows anyone to give any property to any person they wish (or the "close ones", the needy and the orphans in the Quran). In the Quran, inheritance is a complementary procedure made only in the case if bequest didn't cover every material good.
